		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div>Frod,<br><br>Decrepit skin is the main reason I'm in favor of adding some type of downward scaling ability, probably via some type of defensive proc, to warriors.<br><br>However, this isn't something that can be, nor should be addressed via the typical methods- ie, modifying relative melee mitigation values for warriors.&nbsp; Because it's a downward scaling ability, and mitigation is upward scaling, in order to narrow the gap much at all at the low end, the difference would be obscene as melee damage scales upward.<br><br>Also bear in mind that mock alone is a downward scaling ability that absorbs better than half of the theoretical max absorption of decrepit skin.&nbsp; Furthermore, the mana cost of decrepit skin will prevent full-time use, especially if you're in a fast-pulling exp group (I can't maintain all of my utility full time now in a fast pulling exp group, adding in another 15 mana/tick isn't feasible without impacting other abilities, thus, it won't be up full time).<br><div></div><p>Message Edited by josahd on <span class=date_text>03-09-2006</span> <span class=time_text>04:21 PM</span>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175692" target=new>Josahd, Scourge Knight</a>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
