			On paper, ward of tunare is more powerful than decrepit skin.<br><br>Until you realize that it doesn't stack with reptile.&nbsp; Of course that's irrelevant if there's not a druid around, or they're busy with other targets.... for main tanking on a raid, I'm willing to bet most of the time there's a druid around.&nbsp; In a group setting, especially with no druid in the group, ward of tunare beats decrepit skin by quite a bit.<br><blockquote><i>"I'm trying to understand the meaning of the first part of the
statement.&nbsp;&nbsp; Mock's max absorption is 500hp.&nbsp; If I understand
correctly, you're saying that it absorbs a max of 1k per minute if cast
twice per minute, or 4k for the 4-ish mins max duration of Decrepit
Skin."<br></i></blockquote>If it's only the first 2 hits, then you're right- for some reason I had the impression it absorbed up to 250 from the first 3 hits.<br><br>I'm not certain it's as big of an issue as you think it is, but I do think that if powerful defensive procs are going into the game for any of the tanks, it's fair for all the tanks to get them.&nbsp; Frankly, I'd like to hang on to decrepit skin as a tanking tool.&nbsp; If 2 of the tank classes possess these abilities, it's potentially unbalancing- thus, all 3 tanks should get a variant of the defensive proc theme that's roughly equivalent to what the others get.&nbsp; Easiest thing to do is probably just reduce aura of runes' recast timer to be less than its duration, give it the same proc rate mod as ward of tunare/decrepit skin, and make sure its endurance cost is in line so it can be used about as frequently under normal circumstances as ward of tunare/decrepit skin.<br><div></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175692" target=new>Josahd, Scourge Knight</a>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
