			>
			<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
Heimdall-RN wrote:</P>
<P>Yeah but I was told you can't cast 2 spells a fight because you lose your melee agro.&nbsp; Now I'm being told you don't even melee because you're busy chain casting 4 stuns all fight long.<BR>
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>No, no, no... you're confusing two issues.&nbsp; We lose out on melee DPS and swing aggro... which is exactly what we give up for significant spell aggro and the utility our spells offer.</P>
<P>What you fail to realize is that while relying on melee aggro can be cumborsome and sketchy for the first few seconds of a fight (and much less with Mock introduced), along with your insta-cast aggro disciplines, you have a much higher potential for melee DPS... and rightfully so.&nbsp; So going back to the argument this stemmed from, a swords ratio is not its DPS potential for most Knights... </P>
<P>You can't hold two different things against us, when they're in direct competition with each other.&nbsp; You love to do the math, but you can't argue our highest potential melee DPS in the weapon ratio/shieldmate thread&nbsp;and argue about our highest potential aggro in an aggro argument, when you can never practically reach either of those potentials at the same time.</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=790661" target="_blank">
<img src="http://img219.echo.cx/img219/3240/darksig5zj.png" border="0" alt="" /> </a>
