			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
togam wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>&nbsp;</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>sure&nbsp; you can&nbsp; .&nbsp;if&nbsp; you&nbsp; are using&nbsp;aggro&nbsp; specific weapons available to&nbsp; you ie .blade of war&nbsp; in&nbsp; PoP&nbsp; progression&nbsp; level , you&nbsp; find&nbsp; knights&nbsp; (&nbsp; specifically&nbsp; shadowknights )&nbsp; have the&nbsp; same (or better)&nbsp;aggro&nbsp; as warriors with&nbsp; very&nbsp; similar&nbsp; dps (dependant on&nbsp; similar&nbsp; offensive aa's ) so the spell casting&nbsp; aggro&nbsp;advantage &nbsp;would be directly&nbsp; traded off&nbsp; for melee damage . this is how it&nbsp; should be .&nbsp;</P>
<P><FONT color=#0066ff>Have you tried playing a knight and relying on melee for aggro?&nbsp; It doesn't work.&nbsp; It doesn't matter what weapon setup we have..... it doesn't work.&nbsp; Warriors gain more aggro thru melee than Knights do, and melee aggro wasn't enough, hence the advent of your combat ablities for hate generation.&nbsp; How are you going to tell us that ours is enough then?</FONT></P>
<P>since knights have weapons with&nbsp; GREATER&nbsp; ratio&nbsp; and&nbsp; choose to&nbsp; use procs designed &nbsp;to&nbsp; enhance survivability&nbsp; instead of aggro , the dps&nbsp; and survvability&nbsp; is excess to&nbsp; what&nbsp; warriors&nbsp; need . IF&nbsp; you&nbsp; can&nbsp; say&nbsp; that&nbsp; the weapon&nbsp; ratio isn't&nbsp; meaningful&nbsp; then&nbsp; knight&nbsp; weapons can&nbsp; be set&nbsp; to&nbsp; what&nbsp; warriors&nbsp; use giving&nbsp; warriors dps&nbsp; advantage significant&nbsp; enough&nbsp; to offset spellbook&nbsp; advantage , or warrior weapons should be set&nbsp; to&nbsp; knight&nbsp; levels to&nbsp; offset&nbsp; spellbook&nbsp; advantage , either&nbsp; of these 2&nbsp; solutions would probably&nbsp; be acceptable to&nbsp; warriors ,&nbsp; but&nbsp; probably&nbsp; would be very&nbsp; distasteful&nbsp; to&nbsp; most&nbsp; knights&nbsp;because&nbsp; of damage to knight&nbsp; advantage .</P>
<P><FONT color=#0066ff>So I should ask for my hopebringer to be changed from a little group heal to EB instead?&nbsp; The weapon ratio is meaningful because it is one of the things that helps buffer the loss of melee from casting, without it, the melee we do goes down even further.&nbsp; We lose swings in order to maintain aggro, that is simple fact.&nbsp; Perhaps you don't understand this because you don't make that sacrifice for aggro, your main source of aggro is thru swinging your weapon which is quite opposite.&nbsp; So there is no "boost this to offset the spellbook" line you can apply because you are trying to twist things that aren't true.&nbsp; </FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#0066ff>But if you don't believe me, feel free to try to play a knight, get an aggro weapon with aggro augs and maintain aggro without using spells.&nbsp; Experiencing this first-hand goes alot further than having it told you.</FONT><BR></P><BR>
<HR>
