ere there wil be no repercusions for overnuking.&quot;</strong></em></p><p>I'm going to quate that to you the next time I see you complaining about Warriro aggro. Your Working as intended, group with better players</p><p><em><strong>&quot;SoE is not responsible to give classes that tank group mobs tools that make up for others not knowing how to play their classes.&quot;</strong></em></p><p>Soe is however responsible to give us tools that scale according to level increases. Warriors received several increases to their aggro tools when the level was raised to 70, as did Shadow Knights. Paladin tools were left static as there was an artificial cap on Stun Hate.</p><p>Again, the same can be said of Warriors, Mock is good enough, it's the enchanter's fault for not letting you build aggro before he slows.</p><p><em>&quot;Find any Knight that has made the same effort as most raid Warirors make to obtain and hold aggro&quot;</em></p><p>I did, I searched and searched for my very bestest Duel Wield set-up, especially for you, and with my barrage of procs from both weapons I can aggro anything in the game. I encourage all other Paladins out there to switch to a duel Wield set-up.</p>	
