		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			"When pressed with the problem of having to spam stuns...."<br><br>Paladins did not have to spam stuns. Increasing the aggro by 1/3rd and increasing the refresh by 1/3rd cuts the need to spam by 1/3rd sir by <u>any</u> definition.<br><br>"...and STILL LOOSE
AGGRO,"<br>I've played a mid-level Paladin and had other's spells on during raids.
I have yet to see a Paladin forced to spam stuns unless he was trying to wrest aggro from another tank , trying to hold aggro in the
short term against an overnuking/too early nuking Wizard, or trying to
play Wariror vs a raid boss mob with everyone in the raid dumping DPS on it.<br>
<br>
"....our Stuns (used for other purposes as well)...."<br><br>So sir, do you admit stuns are much more powerful than say Bazu and generations of Warrior aggro weapons with things like Anger III on them? That you haver been <u>enormously</u> advantaged for years?<br><br>Did you hide your stuns when Paladins were petitioning for defensive disciplines?<br><br>"Paladins wanted Stun Aggro to scale like every other Tank's aggro tools...."<br><br>Could you explain please how my Bazu scales? I thought I needed a new discipline as content got harder. Say something like Mock - that has LESS aggro sir - nice scaling.<br><br>Paladins looked for a reason/justification/tag line that they could use to campaign for improvemenst they did not need in hopes that they would once again out aggro Warirors as well as outbuff, out heal, out res, and out avoid/mitigate in stunable content with their multi-purpose "aggro spells" and shields and Shield Block they campaigned to deny Warirors practical use of.<br><br>Your stuns have been proven to be overpowered, get used to their reduced utility.<br><br>"I'm going to quate that to you the next time I see you complaining about Warriro aggro."<br><br>Link me your aggro setup - your maximum swing aggro weapon with aggro augs, Symbol of the Planesmaster/Aten's glovea, and EoA item OR show me where you have written a post asking for Paladin Epic 2.0 to have an aggro proc, aggro focus, your post requesting your next self weapon buff to have an aggro component, and your post asking for EoA to be put on a Paladin item before even thinking about saying "Aggro" to a Warrior again sir.<br><br>"I encourage all other Paladins out there to switch to a duel Wield set-up."<br>I encourage them to take what steps they can to improve their aggro insted of expecting an Aggro Free Ride and the ability to use beneficial procs on their weapons and cast group heals while tanking.<br><br>But, IF you want to have to obtain 2 1H aggro weapons, neither of which are worth a wam glob of bazu blood when used with a shield, 3 aggro augs, give up a focus slot for EoA, have to use aggro procs insted of beneficial procs, have to obtain Symbol of the Planesmasters/Aten's Glove's have almost all of you aggro spells/disciplines do nothing except generate aggro, do 1/10th the maximum hit of a Paladin for a tiny fraction of his offensive discipline's duration, etc....<br><br>Petition SoE for Paladins to have to <u>chose</u> between Wariror-like and Cleric-like builds by shutting off some AA abilities when chosing others and losing capability in one to gain capability in the other <u>instead</u> of circling the Wariror Class Description like flies near a rump roast AND having powerful clerical spells.<br><div></div>	
		</td></tr>
